Hi, I'd like to migrate from 2.3 to 2.4 but I found (what I presume to be) an error which can be reproduced using this snippet:

``` java
  @Test
  public void testEuropeBerlin2010() {
    DateTimeZone berlinTimeZone = DateTimeZone.forID("Europe/Berlin");
    Interval berlinInterval = new Interval(
            new DateTime(2010, 10, 31, 0, 0, 0, berlinTimeZone),
            new DateTime(2010, 11,  1, 0, 0, 0, berlinTimeZone) );
    assertEquals(25, berlinInterval.toDuration().toStandardHours().getHours());
  }

  @Test
  public void testAfricaCairo2010() {
    DateTimeZone cairoTimeZone = DateTimeZone.forID("Africa/Cairo");
    Interval cairoInterval = new Interval(
            new DateTime(2010, 8, 10, 0, 0, 0, cairoTimeZone),
            new DateTime(2010, 8, 11, 0, 0, 0, cairoTimeZone) );
    assertEquals(25, cairoInterval.toDuration().toStandardHours().getHours());
  }
```

Test "testAfricaCairo2010" passes with 2.3 and fails with 2.4.
According to http://www.timeanddate.com/time/change/egypt/cairo?year=2010 this looks like an error.
